WEBVTT

00:02.120 --> 00:04.646
WOMAN [ON TV]:
Joe Carroll took hostages inside death row.

00:05.600 --> 00:06.726
[SCREAMS]

00:06.880 --> 00:08.962
You asked me if you were in my dreams.

00:09.320 --> 00:10.924
You are. We're friends.

00:11.080 --> 00:12.844
- And?
- And you're teaching me to kill.

00:13.560 --> 00:15.528
You are my real legacy, Ryan.

00:15.720 --> 00:18.803
I can die knowing
that I will live on through you.

00:18.960 --> 00:21.088
I don't want to lose you, Deb.
I'm gonna do better.

00:21.280 --> 00:22.520
I'll be out in a minute.

00:22.920 --> 00:26.641
- I'm gonna put you out of your misery.
- No. I know how to get to Mike Weston.

00:26.880 --> 00:29.281
DAISY: Well, according to this,
somebody's watching Max.

00:29.480 --> 00:32.086
- Somebody we can use to get to Mike.
- I have the BIA.

00:32.280 --> 00:35.568
If someone is using the laptop,
we can find them in real time.

00:37.720 --> 00:41.202
- The signal just disappeared.
- Why do you think Theo reached out to Joe?

00:41.400 --> 00:44.370
He's getting ready to come after me,
he'll need help to survive.

00:44.600 --> 00:48.491
- Taking on Ryan Hardy and the FBI is crazy.
- We'll need to move quickly on this.

00:48.680 --> 00:50.808
- What the hell are we gonna do?
- I have a plan.

00:50.960 --> 00:52.769
Why do you need this notebook?
What's in it?

00:52.960 --> 00:56.009
A name. Someone with the power
to give me my anonymity back.

00:56.240 --> 00:58.641
- After I take out Ryan Hardy.
- Here's to you.

00:58.840 --> 01:00.410
No. Here's to us.

01:03.760 --> 01:05.125
[GASPS]

01:09.200 --> 01:10.690
[GRUNTS]

01:10.880 --> 01:12.723
[EKG FLATLINING]

01:15.520 --> 01:17.443
[GROANS]

01:24.200 --> 01:25.326
[GRUNTS]

01:48.160 --> 01:50.288
JEWEL:
Sneaking out?

01:50.600 --> 01:52.125
Yeah.

01:52.320 --> 01:54.004
I gotta...

01:54.440 --> 01:56.283
...get home.
- I get it.

01:56.520 --> 01:59.364
I don't normally do this either...

02:00.040 --> 02:01.769
...but last night...

02:02.480 --> 02:05.211
...you seemed so sad.

02:05.400 --> 02:07.801
I didn't think you should be alone.

02:08.000 --> 02:09.729
Yeah, you're right.

02:10.840 --> 02:12.251
But...

02:13.960 --> 02:15.928
...I shouldn't have been here either.

02:30.680 --> 02:31.806
GWEN:
Ryan?

02:32.040 --> 02:34.771
I've been worried to death,
calling you all night.

02:36.160 --> 02:37.650
You're hurt.

02:42.840 --> 02:45.605
You've been drinking? What happened?

02:51.320 --> 02:52.560
Where were you last night?

02:53.400 --> 02:54.970
I screwed up.

02:55.320 --> 02:56.924
Did you...?

03:00.040 --> 03:01.849
How could you do this to us?

03:02.040 --> 03:07.444
- I'm sorry. It's just, after Joe's execution...
- Stop. You do not get to blame him for this.

03:07.640 --> 03:09.927
I told you to stay away from Joe.

03:10.160 --> 03:12.162
I begged you to come home to me.

03:12.680 --> 03:14.921
- And now you've ruined us.
- No.

03:15.120 --> 03:18.442
- No. I can make this right.
- How?

03:18.640 --> 03:23.248
He's dead and you can't let him go.
He owns a part of you that I can't reach.

03:23.440 --> 03:25.886
You know what? I'm tired of trying.

03:26.080 --> 03:28.082
No. Gwen, please.

03:28.280 --> 03:30.647
- You gotta give me a chance.
- I have. Several.

03:33.440 --> 03:35.010
I'm done.

03:36.080 --> 03:38.208
No, no, no. Wait.

03:43.400 --> 03:44.447
MAN:
Don't worry.

03:44.920 --> 03:46.445
You still have me.

03:58.840 --> 04:01.446
This is stupid. You're gonna
grab Mike in broad daylight?

04:01.640 --> 04:03.847
I'm done waiting. I wanna make him suffer.

04:04.040 --> 04:06.520
Let's just take a beat
and be smart about this.

04:06.760 --> 04:09.650
Someone has my laptop.
They're using it to watch Max.

04:09.840 --> 04:12.491
They could be an ally.
We can use them to blindside Mike.

04:12.680 --> 04:14.842
- Get him to come to us.
- That'll take too long.

04:15.040 --> 04:17.771
- Mark, please.
- I'm not Mark!

04:20.120 --> 04:22.441
Yes, you are.

04:22.840 --> 04:25.047
And your heart is broken.

04:25.280 --> 04:29.171
And I understand that. But if you
take a run at Mike now, you'll die.

04:29.360 --> 04:31.522
I'll be on my own again.
I don't know how to do this alone.

04:31.680 --> 04:33.444
Killing him is all I think about.

04:33.640 --> 04:36.962
You don't think that I wanna kill Ryan
for what he did to Kyle?

04:37.280 --> 04:40.841
We're in the same place, Mark.

04:41.360 --> 04:44.125
Okay? We both defined ourselves
by another person.

04:44.320 --> 04:46.209
And now they're dead and we're lost.

04:46.400 --> 04:48.721
But there has to be more than revenge.

04:48.880 --> 04:49.927
[SIGHS]

04:52.800 --> 04:54.211
Like what?

04:58.120 --> 04:59.610
I don't know. But...

04:59.800 --> 05:01.962
But I know that Kyle would want me to live.

05:03.280 --> 05:05.442
To try and find happiness.

05:06.080 --> 05:09.926
And I'm sure that Luke
would want the same for you.

05:19.720 --> 05:21.165
- Mark, no.
- I have to...

05:22.120 --> 05:23.326
...for Luke.

05:48.920 --> 05:51.810
- What are you doing?
- He's got a security detail with him.

05:53.320 --> 05:54.810
That was almost the end, Mark.

05:55.040 --> 05:57.486
You would been dead,
and Mike would've won.

05:58.400 --> 06:00.402
All right. We'll do it your way.

06:01.200 --> 06:03.441
- I'll see you later.
WESTON: Hey.

06:03.640 --> 06:04.687
What's up?

06:09.680 --> 06:13.162
- You heard from Ryan?
- Not since yesterday. He's not in yet?

06:13.480 --> 06:15.801
Well, I'll give him a call
after I talk to Sloan.

06:16.000 --> 06:18.651
I've eliminated her from the list
of possible moles.

06:18.840 --> 06:20.604
I wanna bring her in on the investigation.

06:20.760 --> 06:22.480
- We could use an extra set of eyes.
- Yeah.

06:22.600 --> 06:23.726
[PHONE RINGING]

06:24.920 --> 06:26.649
- Gwen?
- Hey.

06:26.840 --> 06:27.966
Is everything all right?

06:29.000 --> 06:30.729
Ryan's been drinking again.

06:31.720 --> 06:33.165
- Drinking?
- Yeah.

06:33.360 --> 06:36.045
And I can't be there for him anymore.

06:36.240 --> 06:39.767
I just can't.
So somebody probably should be.

06:40.080 --> 06:41.525
Okay.

06:41.920 --> 06:44.241
I'll head over there now. Are you okay?

06:45.720 --> 06:47.563
Not really.

06:52.160 --> 06:54.083
[DOORBELL BUZZING]

06:56.640 --> 06:58.085
Gwen?

07:02.160 --> 07:04.686
[DOOR OPENING]

07:07.200 --> 07:09.851
Remind me to get that key back from you.

07:10.800 --> 07:13.485
- What are you doing here, Max?
- Gwen called me.

07:15.120 --> 07:17.487
- How is she?
- She's upset.

07:17.680 --> 07:19.250
She's worried about you.

07:21.320 --> 07:22.560
What? You've been drinking?

07:23.080 --> 07:25.447
- What are you doing?
- I don't wanna go into it right now.

07:25.640 --> 07:30.646
I love you too much to let you get away
with this, so let's call a sponsor.

07:30.880 --> 07:32.609
Why don't we go to a meeting?

07:32.840 --> 07:35.684
I'm good, really.

07:38.880 --> 07:41.531
I don't know what type of game
Joe was running on you yesterday.

07:41.680 --> 07:43.808
But he's finally gone, you are free.

07:44.000 --> 07:46.606
- You should be relieved.
- You should get back to work.

07:47.400 --> 07:49.528
That's not gonna happen.
You're stuck with me.

07:49.720 --> 07:52.246
I don't need a babysitter, Max.

07:53.240 --> 07:57.131
The tip Joe gave you about Theo being born
from violence in Philadelphia...

07:57.920 --> 07:59.331
...we got a lead.

08:01.720 --> 08:03.245
That's great.

08:03.800 --> 08:06.531
I ran all crime reports
from the years of Theo's childhood.

08:06.720 --> 08:11.203
And I found a multiple murder
some 25 years ago in Philly.

08:11.400 --> 08:13.801
Entire family was slaughtered
except the oldest son.

08:16.520 --> 08:19.205
Terrance Jackson, the sole survivor.

08:19.760 --> 08:21.524
This is Theo.

08:22.800 --> 08:25.770
He pointed to his mother's
abusive boyfriend as a suspect.

08:25.960 --> 08:30.045
Domestic violence, but he had an alibi,
so the case went unsolved.

08:31.840 --> 08:35.322
Six years later they found the boyfriend's
body floating in Tinicum marsh.

08:36.080 --> 08:38.525
- Cause of death?
- Inconclusive.

08:39.080 --> 08:42.208
This could've been Theo's first kill.
He would've been 16 years old.

08:42.400 --> 08:44.721
Revenge for his family's murder,
fits his profile.

08:46.280 --> 08:47.964
What happened to Terrance Jackson?

08:48.160 --> 08:49.650
After 16, he ceased to exist.

08:49.880 --> 08:51.928
No school records, no foster homes,
nothing.

08:52.120 --> 08:53.849
Created a new identity.

08:57.880 --> 08:59.370
Where are you going?

09:01.960 --> 09:03.724
Shower.

09:05.000 --> 09:07.810
- Could you make me some coffee?
- Sure.

09:11.080 --> 09:12.844
[KEYBOARD CLACKING
AND COMPUTER BEEPING]

09:16.520 --> 09:17.931
You doing your homework?

09:18.520 --> 09:21.603
GPS coordinates trace back
to this house in Annapolis.

09:22.000 --> 09:24.890
That's fancy. Who lives there?

09:25.120 --> 09:27.487
Ownership's hidden
behind layers of shell companies.

09:27.640 --> 09:29.529
I haven't been able to unravel them all.

09:29.680 --> 09:32.001
But it's safe to say there's a lot
of money and power behind it.

09:32.200 --> 09:34.851
The kind of money and power
that can help us disappear.

09:35.000 --> 09:36.968
Okay. So, what's the plan?

09:38.920 --> 09:40.445
How'd you like to go for a drive?

09:40.680 --> 09:43.968
- Can we get breakfast on the way?
- Sure.

09:46.680 --> 09:50.127
MARK: Do you trust this guy?
- No. He was a friend of Julianna's.

09:50.320 --> 09:52.721
He gave us the cameras
for Max's apartment...

09:52.920 --> 09:54.763
...set up the web portal
to stream the feed.

09:54.920 --> 09:57.048
He should be able to tell us
who's watching it.

09:57.240 --> 09:58.651
MARK:
Um...

09:59.160 --> 10:01.208
I think Luke should be here for this one.

10:01.360 --> 10:03.089
You don't need him, you can do this.

10:03.280 --> 10:06.921
I know, but he was always good
at this kind of stuff.

10:07.800 --> 10:09.609
Sure. Whatever you need.

10:24.280 --> 10:25.770
Hey, Silas.

10:26.120 --> 10:28.168
Whoa, not cool.

10:28.360 --> 10:30.488
- You need to go.
- Don't be like that.

10:30.680 --> 10:33.365
I just need help with something,
then we'll be on our way.

10:33.560 --> 10:36.530
Forget it. Did you hear
what some freak did to Julianna?

10:36.720 --> 10:39.007
- Her face was burned off.
MARK: That freak was me.

10:39.200 --> 10:41.168
And her death was a thing of beauty.

10:41.320 --> 10:43.800
- Don't be such a dick about it.
- Take him in the back.

10:44.800 --> 10:46.040
SILAS:
What? No.

10:48.000 --> 10:50.446
MARK:
All right. Okay.

10:51.960 --> 10:53.371
[SILAS GRUNTS]

10:53.520 --> 10:55.887
You know, I just don't get
the whole hipster thing.

10:56.160 --> 10:59.050
Never mind the ironic headwear
and the artisanal pickles.

10:59.240 --> 11:03.370
It just seems stupid to grow something
so flammable on your face.

11:03.520 --> 11:05.409
SILAS: Ah! Ah!
- It didn't have to go this way.

11:06.840 --> 11:09.923
I was all ready to come in here,
flirt with you a little.

11:10.120 --> 11:14.364
SILAS: That's cool. That's cool. Let's just
start over. I'll do whatever you want, okay?

11:15.040 --> 11:16.565
Okay.

11:18.680 --> 11:20.330
But give us any trouble...

11:20.520 --> 11:23.000
...I'm gonna roast marshmallows
off your face.

11:37.560 --> 11:42.202
- Looks like someone's having a party.
- Well, I love parties. We gonna crash?

11:43.240 --> 11:45.004
If only it were that easy.

11:56.440 --> 11:58.442
- No.
- What?

11:58.640 --> 12:00.529
THEO:
We need finesse here, Penny.

12:00.720 --> 12:03.121
- Not mayhem.
- Fine.

12:03.480 --> 12:04.811
Hey. How you doing?

12:05.000 --> 12:07.367
- Can we help you, sir?
- I sure hope so. We're lost.

12:07.560 --> 12:09.528
And our navigation system is on the fritz.

12:09.720 --> 12:13.202
You pay all this money for technology,
it screws you when you need it most.

12:13.400 --> 12:15.880
- Right? Am I right?
- Sir, this is private property.

12:16.080 --> 12:17.889
Can't be here. You need to leave now.

12:18.040 --> 12:21.601
No problem. You wouldn't happen to know
how to get to 97 from here would you?

12:21.840 --> 12:23.171
- Can't help you.
- Okay.

12:23.360 --> 12:25.249
- Now.
- All right. Have a nice day.

12:26.040 --> 12:27.724
We could've taken him.

12:28.000 --> 12:29.047
That's not the point.

12:29.920 --> 12:34.482
You can't just hop the fence.
Which means we gotta find another way in.

12:41.120 --> 12:43.248
- Hey.
- How's he doing?

12:43.440 --> 12:44.851
It's not good.

13:06.560 --> 13:08.050
- You okay?
- Yeah.

13:08.200 --> 13:09.440
WESTON:
You could've called me.

13:09.640 --> 13:11.688
You know you can talk to me
about anything.

13:11.880 --> 13:14.247
I know. Let's get to work.

13:17.240 --> 13:19.083
WESTON:
Max was catching me up on the latest.

13:19.240 --> 13:22.926
Yeah. I noticed some things in this file
that just does not add up.

13:23.120 --> 13:25.487
- Like?
- Well, look at the victims' bodies.

13:25.680 --> 13:29.401
Legs straight, together.
Arms extended over their heads.

13:29.600 --> 13:32.444
- They were posed post-mortem.
- But the autopsy report says...

13:32.640 --> 13:36.884
...that the violence was focused, directed,
methodical, not erratic.

13:37.120 --> 13:39.521
That's atypical for an abusive boyfriend.

13:39.720 --> 13:42.451
Wait a minute, there's broken mirror
in the house.

13:42.640 --> 13:45.041
Any victim injuries consistent
with broken glass?

13:45.240 --> 13:46.924
No. Definitely not.

13:47.120 --> 13:49.646
- Was the mirror significant?
- Yeah.

13:50.240 --> 13:53.130
I've seen it before.
It matches the M.O. of a serial killer...

13:53.320 --> 13:56.529
...who was active in Philadelphia
in the '90s. Called the Madman.

13:56.720 --> 13:59.451
- What do we know about him?
- Never been caught.

13:59.640 --> 14:02.120
Former colleague of mine, Lisa Campbell,
had the case.

14:02.360 --> 14:05.284
And I think she's an academy instructor
at Quantico now.

14:05.880 --> 14:07.644
This is how we're gonna get Theo.

14:10.960 --> 14:14.009
LISA: The broken mirror does play
into the Madman's signature.

14:14.200 --> 14:17.044
- So this could be one of his?
LISA: It's possible.

14:18.080 --> 14:20.731
But you didn't fly all the way down here
for a cold case.

14:20.960 --> 14:23.770
- What's really going on?
- Terrance, the surviving member...

14:24.000 --> 14:26.321
...vanished from the grid
when he was 16 years old.

14:26.520 --> 14:28.841
We think he became Theo Noble.

14:30.400 --> 14:33.768
So how does solving this case
get you to him?

14:33.960 --> 14:36.531
Okay, so here's my theory.

14:36.760 --> 14:41.004
A 10-year-old Theo believes his family has
been murdered by his mother's boyfriend.

14:41.200 --> 14:44.010
Right? So he plots,
he plans for six years to take him out.

14:44.200 --> 14:48.728
I think if we reveal the Madman
to be the family's true killer...

14:48.920 --> 14:52.367
...he won't be able to resist.
He'll come after him. And we'll be waiting.

14:52.560 --> 14:54.244
Use one shark as bait for another.

14:57.600 --> 14:59.648
I'll pull all my files.

15:02.400 --> 15:04.562
[PHONE RINGING]

15:06.280 --> 15:07.691
SLOAN: Hey, Tom?
- Hey.

15:07.920 --> 15:08.967
Sorry to bother you.

15:09.160 --> 15:12.403
Just doing some housekeeping
on the incident reports from the raid...

15:12.640 --> 15:14.847
...at Mark Gray's Brooklyn safe house.

15:15.040 --> 15:17.361
Do you have a minute to come by
the command center?

15:17.560 --> 15:21.724
Um, I'm actually off-site right now.
Can I call you right back?

15:21.920 --> 15:24.161
While I've got you,
can I ask a couple questions?

15:24.360 --> 15:25.441
Yeah, I'm kind of busy.

15:25.600 --> 15:26.931
It would really help me out.

15:29.000 --> 15:30.650
All right, what is this about?

15:30.840 --> 15:33.161
Just crossing T's and dotting I's.

15:33.360 --> 15:35.761
You helped clear
the Gray safe house, right?

15:35.960 --> 15:38.440
- Yeah.
- Which floor?

15:39.600 --> 15:42.570
- First floor.
- And were you up on the second floor at all?

15:42.760 --> 15:46.446
- I probably passed through with my partner.
- So you were never alone up there?

15:46.880 --> 15:49.087
- No, no.
- Okay. Good.

15:49.280 --> 15:52.250
- Yeah, that's what it says here in your report.
- Okay, cool.

15:52.440 --> 15:56.604
- Let me know if you need anything else.
- Will do. Thanks.

15:58.760 --> 16:00.683
If the Madman really did
attack his family...

16:00.840 --> 16:03.844
...then Terrance or Theo
is very lucky to be alive.

16:04.040 --> 16:06.691
He's ever only left one other survivor.

16:06.880 --> 16:10.327
She described the suspect as
medium build, dark hair, work boots.

16:10.520 --> 16:11.851
- Anything else?
- No.

16:12.040 --> 16:14.930
She didn't get a good look at him.
The lights were out.

16:19.800 --> 16:21.370
Hang on.

16:22.760 --> 16:26.924
Philadelphia Department of Water and Power
van parked outside the Jackson house?

16:27.080 --> 16:29.606
What were you saying about the lights
in the building in that other case?

16:29.800 --> 16:32.160
Their power had been shut off.
They hadn't paid their bills.

16:32.200 --> 16:33.611
Utility workers are practically invisible.

16:33.840 --> 16:36.525
Unfettered access to buildings,
come and go as they please.

16:36.760 --> 16:38.285
It's a perfect camouflage.

16:38.480 --> 16:40.721
We need to go through
the other Madman cases...

16:40.920 --> 16:43.161
...and see if there was
any DWP activity nearby.

16:43.360 --> 16:46.170
- Worth checking out.
- I'll reach out to Philadelphia DWP.

16:46.400 --> 16:48.482
Look for records of service
during the attacks.

16:48.640 --> 16:50.449
- I'm gonna head up to Philly.
- We'll head up to Philly.

16:50.640 --> 16:51.971
- We're going too.
- No.

16:52.160 --> 16:53.685
Stay here. Get us a name.

16:53.880 --> 16:55.325
Call if you get something.

16:58.240 --> 17:02.211
- You think he ditched us on purpose?
- I hope not.

17:15.560 --> 17:19.770
Sorry, you know, they didn't have
macrobiotic chalupas.

17:20.200 --> 17:22.567
Penny, you need to grow up.

17:22.760 --> 17:23.965
This is serious.

17:24.280 --> 17:26.964
No. You're serious. This
is what we make it.

17:27.160 --> 17:31.131
You know what your problem is, T? You
need everything to be perfect all the time.

17:31.360 --> 17:32.521
I am spontaneous and fun.

17:32.960 --> 17:35.691
Try reckless and more
than a little immature.

17:36.040 --> 17:38.202
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

17:38.800 --> 17:42.805
Okay, so what is going on inside this
mansion that it needs that much security?

17:43.040 --> 17:45.646
I don't know, but it's
connected to Strauss.

17:46.120 --> 17:49.044
- How do we get in?
- I hacked into all the high-end limousine...

17:49.240 --> 17:51.846
...companies in D.C.
I found five headed to the mansion.

17:52.280 --> 17:54.169
Ran a client list.

17:55.400 --> 17:58.165
- Looks like it could be our younger cousin.
- Exactly.

17:58.360 --> 18:00.442
Meet Daniel Carr. Lobbyist extraordinaire.

18:00.680 --> 18:03.047
And our ticket to the party.

18:12.200 --> 18:14.043
Were you and Luke ever apart as kids?

18:15.280 --> 18:16.566
No.

18:17.120 --> 18:19.487
No, we did everything together.

18:21.800 --> 18:23.564
He was my only friend.

18:23.760 --> 18:26.047
All the other kids thought we were weird.

18:26.240 --> 18:30.962
I was the complete opposite.
I had so many friends growing up. But...

18:31.160 --> 18:34.448
It wasn't until I met Kyle
that I realized how lonely I was.

18:34.680 --> 18:37.251
He gave me the strength
to finally be myself.

18:37.440 --> 18:38.487
I'm jealous.

18:40.760 --> 18:43.445
I don't know who I am without Luke.

18:47.720 --> 18:51.202
You are a smart, sweet man.

18:51.440 --> 18:53.442
And you're strong and you're funny.

18:53.640 --> 18:54.926
And you're a hell of a cook.

18:56.320 --> 19:01.201
And with all this tragedy you've
experienced, you still got a good heart.

19:01.520 --> 19:03.329
And you trusted me.

19:04.880 --> 19:06.609
I'll never forget that.

19:10.840 --> 19:14.287
MAN [ON TV]:... America takes a deep
breath and closes the final chapter...

19:14.440 --> 19:17.569
...in the story of one of the nation's
most notorious and charming murderer.

19:17.840 --> 19:20.650
After a bloody hostage crisis,
defused by Agent Ryan Hardy...

19:20.880 --> 19:23.531
...serial killer Joe Carroll
was executed yesterday.

19:23.720 --> 19:26.121
Carroll terrorized the East Coast,
killing dozens...

19:26.280 --> 19:29.841
...and managed to escape federal custody,
not once, but twice. It was Ryan Hardy...

19:30.000 --> 19:33.209
You shouldn't be working today
after what you went through yesterday.

19:33.440 --> 19:36.364
- I like to keep busy.
- Heh.

19:36.720 --> 19:37.881
If we catch the Madman...

19:38.080 --> 19:40.686
...understand that I'm gonna bring him in
the right way.

19:41.400 --> 19:42.731
You accusing me of something?

19:42.880 --> 19:44.769
No. I just know you like to color
outside the lines.

19:44.920 --> 19:49.084
But this guy killed a lot of people
on my watch, so...

19:49.280 --> 19:51.601
I need a clean conviction.
Gotta do it by the book.

19:52.000 --> 19:53.684
- Of course.
MAN: How can I help you?

19:55.520 --> 19:57.045
I got this. Two rooms please.

19:57.280 --> 19:58.725
[PHONE RINGING]

20:01.040 --> 20:02.246
- Hey, Mike.
- We got a name.

20:02.440 --> 20:04.807
Crosscheck of DWP records show
the lone employee...

20:04.960 --> 20:08.169
...working in the same sector
in at least four of the Madman murders.

20:08.400 --> 20:10.926
Suspect's name is Oleg Vukovich.

20:11.120 --> 20:13.487
Max's sending a picture
and last-known address now.

20:13.680 --> 20:16.604
Should we send a local HRT team
to meet with you and Lisa?

20:23.680 --> 20:24.727
No.

20:24.920 --> 20:26.922
We'll check it out.
We'll call if we need backup.

20:27.120 --> 20:30.488
- Okay. Max and I are on our way there.
LISA: Your guys get anything?

20:31.520 --> 20:33.409
No, no. They're still working on it.

20:33.600 --> 20:35.523
- That's the room key?
- Oh, there you go.

20:35.720 --> 20:38.121
Oh, right. I left something in the car.

20:38.320 --> 20:39.970
- I'll be up in a minute.
- All right.

20:44.120 --> 20:45.849
[TIRES SCREECHING]

20:53.840 --> 20:57.049
FELICITY: This place is far, huh?
- Yes.

20:57.240 --> 20:59.208
But worth the wait.

20:59.440 --> 21:02.046
It's the most exclusive party
you'll ever go to.

21:04.120 --> 21:05.929
Ah, looks like we're here.

21:06.920 --> 21:08.206
I don't see any houses.

21:10.360 --> 21:14.001
DANIEL: Who the hell are you?
- Evening, Daniel. Ma'am.

21:14.160 --> 21:15.366
[SCOFFS]

21:16.000 --> 21:17.161
What is going on?

21:20.880 --> 21:22.803
I've got some questions about this party.

21:23.200 --> 21:25.931
If you know about the party,
you know I can't say anything.

21:26.160 --> 21:28.561
It's easy to talk tough, Daniel.

21:31.960 --> 21:35.601
But I'm a professional at causing pain
and you're an amateur at taking it.

21:35.800 --> 21:38.724
So let's cut to the chase.
Who's hosting the party?

21:41.840 --> 21:44.207
I've only heard a first name.

21:45.080 --> 21:51.804
Eliza. Now, listen to me. These people,
you do not want their attention.

21:52.360 --> 21:54.362
Oh, but that's exactly what I want, Daniel.

21:54.560 --> 21:58.406
Now, both of you get undressed. We don't
wanna get any blood on the clothes.

21:58.560 --> 22:00.005
[FELICITY WHIMPERS]

24:19.960 --> 24:25.922
[WOMAN SCREAMING
AND BLADE SLASHING ON RECORDING]

24:28.400 --> 24:29.890
[RECORDING STOPS]

24:30.200 --> 24:31.690
[FLOOR CREAKING]

24:53.360 --> 24:54.521
[FLOOR CREAKING]

24:54.720 --> 24:56.768
[OLEG GRUNTING]

25:28.440 --> 25:30.727
LISA:
What the hell were you thinking?

25:30.960 --> 25:33.804
You nearly got yourself killed
and the Madman is in the wind.

25:34.000 --> 25:35.843
- We'll find him, all right?
- We had him.

25:36.080 --> 25:38.651
And if you'd followed protocol,
he'd be in custody.

25:40.000 --> 25:41.729
You better talk some sense into him.

25:42.600 --> 25:44.807
- Hey, are you okay?
- I'm fine.

25:45.080 --> 25:47.082
Are you?
They could suspend you for this.

25:47.280 --> 25:48.850
I don't care, okay?

25:49.080 --> 25:50.889
Pull everything you can on Oleg.

25:51.080 --> 25:54.846
Friends, family, other property. Anything!

25:56.080 --> 25:59.243
- I've never seen him like this.
- I have.

26:01.160 --> 26:03.288
[DOORBELL RINGING]

26:09.480 --> 26:10.970
TOM: Hey.
- Sorry, I know it's late.

26:11.120 --> 26:12.963
- Everything okay?
- It's this safe house raid.

26:13.120 --> 26:15.521
Some details aren't adding up
and I'm on a deadline.

26:15.760 --> 26:17.330
You offered to help, is this okay?

26:18.280 --> 26:21.648
- Sure. Sure. Come on in.
- Thanks.

26:24.720 --> 26:26.290
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

26:27.120 --> 26:28.770
SILAS:
I got good news and bad.

26:28.960 --> 26:30.769
Did you find who's watching Max?

26:30.960 --> 26:34.681
No, but I did manage to track
where the laptop's been used.

26:34.880 --> 26:36.291
And that's the bad news.

26:36.480 --> 26:39.689
It's inside the FBI.
Your mystery man works for the feds.

26:39.880 --> 26:41.723
- How long until we identify him?
- Never.

26:41.920 --> 26:44.685
Hacking the FBI firewall
is too black hat for me.

26:44.880 --> 26:47.486
I'm worried I set off an alarm
sniffing around outside.

26:47.680 --> 26:50.923
- See? I told you this was a waste of time.
- No. This still helps us.

26:51.160 --> 26:53.447
We just need to find someone
who can hack the FBI.

26:53.640 --> 26:55.927
You know anyone who does that?
I sure don't.

26:58.200 --> 27:00.043
Actually, I do.

27:21.360 --> 27:23.761
How are we supposed to find
this Eliza chick anyway?

27:24.360 --> 27:27.489
I figure she'll be pretty
close to the action.

27:38.440 --> 27:41.011
- Come on.
- Where we going?

27:48.720 --> 27:50.165
Bracelet.

27:50.320 --> 27:52.766
[BRACELET BLEEPING]

28:01.400 --> 28:02.731
Bracelet.

28:05.280 --> 28:06.725
[BRACELET BLEEPING]

28:06.880 --> 28:08.291
Have fun.

28:27.920 --> 28:30.810
[MAN GRUNTING]

28:33.200 --> 28:35.407
[MAN 1 GRUNTING
AND WOMAN GAGGING]

28:43.600 --> 28:46.763
[MAN 2 WHIMPERING
AND SAW WHIRRING]

28:46.920 --> 28:49.491
[SAW CUTTING AND MAN 2 GRUNTING]

28:59.760 --> 29:04.641
- Sorry, folks, this area is off limits.
- Oh, it's okay. We're just gonna see Eliza.

29:06.320 --> 29:08.129
[MAN GRUNTING]

29:12.520 --> 29:13.965
Are you ready?

29:14.640 --> 29:16.051
Ready.

29:37.200 --> 29:38.361
Who are you?

29:42.320 --> 29:43.845
Theo's as good a name as any.

29:44.880 --> 29:47.201
I've been led to believe
that we have a friend in common.

29:47.520 --> 29:50.683
- I sure I don't know what you mean.
- He was found dead recently...

29:50.880 --> 29:52.564
...after a very public mistrial.

29:54.240 --> 29:57.244
According to the news,
you killed that gentleman.

29:57.480 --> 30:00.086
Dr. Strauss' death was a tragedy...

30:00.520 --> 30:03.524
...brought about by his willingness
to betray those close to him.

30:04.000 --> 30:07.129
A trait I can't imagine
that you would condone.

30:07.880 --> 30:10.850
Certainly not what one
looks for in a friend.

30:12.920 --> 30:16.606
But I'm sure you didn't come all the way
here and shoot my security people...

30:16.840 --> 30:18.842
...just to talk about the dearly departed.

30:19.040 --> 30:20.485
No.

30:22.360 --> 30:23.441
I came to make an offer.

30:23.880 --> 30:26.884
But only once I'm convinced
you're the person to make it to.

30:28.240 --> 30:30.891
Can we cut to the chase already?
My feet are killing me.

30:31.280 --> 30:34.284
- And you are?
- Not the topic of conversation.

30:35.560 --> 30:38.928
I assume you are familiar
with Special Agent Ryan Hardy.

30:39.120 --> 30:41.487
- Vaguely.
- Well, he caught Joe Carroll.

30:41.680 --> 30:42.886
And Arthur Strauss.

30:43.400 --> 30:46.882
And he's come closer than anyone else
to catching me.

30:47.040 --> 30:50.886
Do you really believe
that you can stay off of his radar forever?

30:51.080 --> 30:53.560
For argument's sake,
let's pretend like that matters.

30:53.760 --> 30:57.003
Well, then let's also pretend
that I can deliver him to you.

30:57.200 --> 30:59.009
Dead or alive. Your choice.

30:59.560 --> 31:02.928
Just know that alive
won't necessarily mean whole.

31:05.720 --> 31:09.805
No offense, but why would we outsource
such a sensitive matter?

31:10.000 --> 31:11.764
Because I'm already exposed.

31:12.080 --> 31:17.849
You go after Ryan Hardy and you fail,
you put a target right on your back.

31:18.040 --> 31:20.520
I'm providing you with a firewall of sorts.

31:21.560 --> 31:24.040
Question is: What is that worth to you?

31:24.560 --> 31:28.121
Why do I think
you already have a price in mind?

31:37.320 --> 31:39.288
A discussion for another day.

31:42.840 --> 31:44.365
Sorry about the mess.

32:25.640 --> 32:27.529
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

32:34.560 --> 32:35.766
- Hey.

32:36.080 --> 32:40.529
Listen, I'm giving you a pass because it was
your lead that got us so close to Oleg.

32:40.720 --> 32:44.247
What happened tonight
cannot ever happen again.

32:45.000 --> 32:48.004
- I get it.
- You won't look good in an orange jumpsuit.

32:52.640 --> 32:55.120
BOLOs for Oleg are out across the city.

32:55.360 --> 32:58.569
And all of his financials have been tagged
in case he tries to run.

32:58.760 --> 33:03.209
Yeah, well, his journal indicates that he
suffers from profound psychotic delusions.

33:03.400 --> 33:05.687
He thinks he's Charon,
the boatman of Hades...

33:05.920 --> 33:08.207
...ferrying souls across the River Styx.

33:08.400 --> 33:10.721
What's his compulsion with mirrors?
Why break them?

33:10.960 --> 33:12.007
Scared of them.

33:12.200 --> 33:14.806
He believes they are the gateway to hell.

33:15.280 --> 33:17.123
And he's not ready to go back yet.

33:32.600 --> 33:35.410
- Hi. How can I help you?
- The FBI, what room?

33:35.680 --> 33:39.048
I'm sorry,
I can't just give you that information.

33:40.720 --> 33:44.281
Whoa. Wait a second.
Wait a second. Wait. Ah!

33:44.440 --> 33:46.090
[BODY THUMPS]

33:49.560 --> 33:50.607
[GASPS]

34:01.600 --> 34:02.965
[PHONE LINE RINGING]

34:03.120 --> 34:04.804
[WOMAN SCREAMING ON TAPE]

34:04.960 --> 34:07.486
[RECORDING] Hi, you've reached Gwen.
Please leave a message.

34:08.639 --> 34:10.005
Gwen, it's me.

34:10.199 --> 34:11.929
I need to talk to you.

34:12.120 --> 34:15.442
I can fix this, please.
Please call me back.

34:17.000 --> 34:18.445
I love you.

34:30.560 --> 34:33.210
That call have anything to do
with how you behaved today?

34:33.440 --> 34:34.601
Not at all.

34:34.840 --> 34:37.366
I've left that message before.

34:37.560 --> 34:39.324
Divorced, twice.

34:39.840 --> 34:42.969
Finally realized our work
doesn't leave room for relationships.

34:43.159 --> 34:44.685
It's just one or the other.

34:44.880 --> 34:46.085
I don't believe that.

34:46.719 --> 34:49.803
A word of unsolicited advice:

34:50.960 --> 34:55.090
Just walk away. She'll be better off
and, in the end, so will you.

34:55.639 --> 34:57.165
Yeah, listen.

34:57.400 --> 34:58.845
I'm gonna go downstairs.

34:59.040 --> 35:00.963
Get some air. Do you want anything?

35:01.960 --> 35:05.123
No, I'm gonna take these back to my room.
Will you give me a hand?

35:14.640 --> 35:15.880
[DOOR LOCK BEEPING]

35:19.560 --> 35:21.210
See you tomorrow?

35:30.160 --> 35:31.321
[DOOR LOCK BEEPING]

35:32.000 --> 35:34.571
[SHOWER RUNNING]

36:03.600 --> 36:07.241
WOMAN [ON RECORDING]:
No, please! No!

36:09.160 --> 36:10.207
Hello?

36:10.360 --> 36:11.771
[WOMAN SCREAMING ON RECORDING]

36:11.920 --> 36:13.445
[RECORDING STOPS]

36:41.920 --> 36:44.571
Ryan! Ryan, stop!

36:50.600 --> 36:52.602
RYAN:
So I got a few questions.

36:52.840 --> 36:56.731
November 14th, 1990.
An apartment in Kensington.

36:57.040 --> 36:59.361
A mother. Three children. The Jacksons.

36:59.560 --> 37:00.721
You remember them?

37:06.040 --> 37:08.361
Why would you spare the boy?

37:14.360 --> 37:15.930
You know, I read your journal.

37:18.680 --> 37:20.205
I know how you feel about these.

37:21.960 --> 37:24.361
OLEG:
No. God. Stop!

37:24.560 --> 37:26.722
Not until you tell me why you let him live.

37:26.920 --> 37:29.127
- Because he was my friend.
LISA: Get off him.

37:30.440 --> 37:32.283
What do you mean, "your friend"?

37:32.960 --> 37:35.486
I did some work in his building.

37:35.960 --> 37:37.485
He would hide in the stairs.

37:37.640 --> 37:40.211
Away from his mother
when she hit him.

37:41.640 --> 37:45.804
When I looked in his eyes,
I saw that he was like me.

37:47.320 --> 37:52.963
One day, he asked me to come
and kill his family.

37:54.880 --> 37:56.245
He was a 10 years old.

37:57.000 --> 37:58.650
He was a demon.

37:58.920 --> 38:03.562
He made me promise to kill them all,
except for the little girl.

38:03.800 --> 38:05.848
- Wait. What little girl?
- His sister, Sophia.

38:06.280 --> 38:10.683
- Terrance didn't have a sister. Only brothers.
- She was a foster, taken in for the money.

38:10.920 --> 38:12.081
Why would he protect her?

38:12.280 --> 38:13.884
He loved her.

38:14.080 --> 38:15.411
They shared a special bond.

38:21.680 --> 38:25.366
I come bearing gifts. Still take yours
with milk, sugar and a splash of coffee?

38:25.520 --> 38:27.443
Yeah. Thanks.

38:32.840 --> 38:34.046
What's wrong?

38:35.680 --> 38:38.206
Ryan was drunk. Back at the hotel.

38:41.040 --> 38:44.123
- If Campbell hadn't been there
to stop him... - But she was.

38:46.160 --> 38:48.447
And we'll be there to get him through this.

38:57.920 --> 39:00.924
This hacker guy, he's the one
who killed Strauss?

39:01.200 --> 39:04.170
Yeah.
And he gave me a way to contact him...

39:04.360 --> 39:06.840
...in case I ever heard of anything
that put him in jeopardy.

39:12.720 --> 39:14.324
What's the problem?

39:15.080 --> 39:16.570
This is a scary guy.

39:17.480 --> 39:20.643
Like, maybe the scariest guy I've ever met.

39:22.560 --> 39:24.483
You don't have to stick around.

39:24.680 --> 39:26.409
I can do this by myself.

39:27.680 --> 39:28.761
No.

39:28.960 --> 39:31.361
I owe you. Okay. We're in this together.

39:44.600 --> 39:46.090
You think they'll go for it?

39:46.920 --> 39:48.081
I don't know.

39:48.280 --> 39:50.044
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]

39:54.480 --> 39:55.766
Is that them?

39:56.360 --> 39:57.771
No.

39:59.120 --> 40:00.360
Who is it?

40:03.760 --> 40:05.489
Someone very unexpected.

40:05.680 --> 40:09.287
Agent Ruiz cleared the bedroom
on the second floor here.

40:09.480 --> 40:14.407
And Talley and Hancock searched the
living room and kitchen on the first floor.

40:14.760 --> 40:17.809
So Ruiz is alone on the second floor...

40:18.000 --> 40:20.446
...but protocol states that HRT agents
move in pairs.

40:20.640 --> 40:22.847
- Why wasn't that done here?
- Heat of the moment.

40:23.000 --> 40:25.241
Adrenaline pumping and all that.

40:34.800 --> 40:36.325
What are you looking for?

40:36.560 --> 40:39.404
Trying to find which agent was paired
with Ruiz that day.

40:39.600 --> 40:42.604
- Isn't it right there in my report?
- It was a joint engagement...

40:42.760 --> 40:45.001
...so there's another report
filed by our team.

40:45.160 --> 40:48.767
- A second report?
- Yeah, it's a new policy this year.

40:50.320 --> 40:51.810
Here it is.

40:59.440 --> 41:01.807
TOM: No. No, no. You don't understand.
Let me explain.

41:01.960 --> 41:03.530
[GUNSHOT]

41:03.680 --> 41:05.648
[SLOAN GRUNTING]

41:14.680 --> 41:16.364
No.

41:18.200 --> 41:19.281
No, no, no.

41:19.840 --> 41:21.604
No. No.

41:32.680 --> 41:34.170
[BEEPING]

41:39.200 --> 41:40.690
Gwen?

42:19.880 --> 42:21.325
CARROLL:
Good man.

42:22.200 --> 42:23.611
You're better off without her.

42:27.240 --> 42:30.847
Now, how about a drink?

43:20.320 --> 43:22.322
[English - US - SDH]
